k) to be able to do &quot;some&quot;<br>&gt;    damage *just* because that bug prevents them to play their char as<br>&gt;    it should be played : hand to hand. Same for dimach reload<br>&gt;    time...Dimach for MA is the same as full auto, or burst, for weapon<br>&gt;    users...and we both know those 2 skills dont take 30 minutes to<br>&gt;    recharge. The MA doesnt have both skills, but just one, and it<br>&gt;    takes forever to use. You can say &quot;yeah, but MA's have their<br>&gt;    special attacks&quot; : true!! Nice addition by the way! BUT : those<br>&gt;    special attacks : would it be possible to have them hit for more<br>&gt;    then 1 damage most of the time?..<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :o --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/embarassed.gif ALT=":o"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>&gt;<br>&gt; As i said i'm quite new to the game, so didnt notice all this, and<br>&gt;    when i read the board i though &quot;bah, we'll see later on if that is<br>&gt;    really a problem&quot;. Well, i'm only lvl 21 right now, and it already<br>&gt;    started. In a mission yesterday i had 2 horrible fights, where i<br>&gt;    constantly hit 2 targets in a row for minimal damage 20, 20, 20, 40<br>&gt;    brawl, 20, 20, 20. I can imagine what this can be at later<br>&gt;    levels...<br>&gt;<br>&gt; So could we just get an answer on this topic? I chose this character<br>&gt;    for its power, it's finesse and speed. If i wanted to be forced to<br>&gt;    use a huge hammer or kill baddies with a shotgun, i certainly<br>&gt;    wouldnt have taken a Martial Artist..<br>&gt;<br>&gt; Thanx for reading (if you did)<br>&gt;<br>&gt; Regards<br><br>It's true i'm not really &quot;old&quot; in AO, but read alot of forums (dont tell my boss hehe)<br>The answer : <br><br>Hello,<br><br>I cannot give you an official statemet because of obious reasons I am<br>not the person with the authority or knowledge of such issues.<br>I can tell you that there are no plans that I am aware of that changes<br>like theese will come to the MA proffession. But on the other hand I do<br>not know what is planned for the next patches.<br>Regarding the bug: I thought it was gone, but if you say it is still<br>there then I guess it is. I will take a look into the matters and see<br>what I can find.<br>Sorry for the inconvieniences.<br><br>So is this minimal damage thing a bug, or is it a &quot;feature&quot; due to AC calculation? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/utoymas69.showPublicProfile?language=EN>toymas69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#660000>(12/7/01 7:12:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1461.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /me is utopist and wrote to Funcom..got an answer</span><hr size=1> <br>This is true???<br>who wrote the reply?<br>and - HEY SENSEI - NEWS STORY FOR U ! ! !<br><br><br>Katzy LvL27 MA<br>CLAN RK2  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uhoppasi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hoppasi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#660000>(12/7/01 7:31:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1461.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /me is utopist and wrote to Funcom..got an answer</span><hr size=1> Aleksander S. Grøndal aka (BlueOffset)<br>Funcom Customer Service<br>&lt;<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://community.anarchy-online.com>">community.anarchy-onlin